## Premiere Pro UXP `getMarkers` for Sequence Markers

### API Reference

The `getMarkers` function in UXP returns a Markers object for a Sequence or ProjectItem. The signature is:
```typescript
getMarkers(markerOwnerObject: Sequence | ClipProjectItem): Promise<Markers>
```

### Related Actions
You can also use `createMoveMarkerAction(marker: Marker, tickTime: TickTime)` to move a marker to a new time value, and `createAddMarkerAction(Name: string, markerType?, startTime?, duration?, comments?)` to add a new marker.

### Important Notes

In Premiere Pro, all markers and metadata associated with trackItems are actually attached to the backing projectItem; it's not possible to have different markers and metadata for each trackItem.(no content)As of November 2025, Premiere Pro has moved to extensibility based on UXP (Unified Extensibility Platform). ExtendScript-based integrations are still supported through September 2026.

### Getting Started with UXP Development

The Premiere Pro UXP API documentation is available at: https://developer.adobe.com/premiere-pro/uxp/(no content)To develop UXP plugins, you'll need the Premiere Pro BETA build and the UXP Developer Tool, both available through Creative Cloud Desktop.

### Example Usage Pattern (Based on API Signatures)

```javascript
// Get the require function for ppro module
const { app } = require("ppro");

async function getSequenceMarkers() {
    // Get the active sequence
    const sequence = await app.project.getActiveSequence();

    // Get markers for the sequence
    const markers = await app.getMarkers(sequence);

    // Work with the markers object
    // (iterate, read properties, etc.)
}
```

To see TypeScript definitions for the API, you can add typescript definitions to the .js file in which you are working. This allows you to see and use TypeScript definitions for Premiere Pro's UXP APIs in Visual Studio Code.

For the most complete and up-to-date example code, I'd recommend checking the official [Adobe UXP Premiere Pro samples repository](https://github.com/AdobeDocs/uxp-premiere-pro-samples) and the [official API documentation](https://developer.adobe.com/premiere-pro/uxp/ppro_reference/classes/markers/).


